<div class="widget">
  <div class="widget-header">
    <i class="icon-flag"></i>
      <h3>Messages</h3>
  </div> <!-- /widget-header -->

  <div class="widget-content">
    <% if @period_default > 0 %>
      <div class="accordion" id="accordion2">
        <div class="accordion-group">
          <div class="accordion-heading">
            <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapse1">
              <div class="alert">
                <p>A default <strong>'Performance Review Period'</strong>has been created. Please change the 'Performance Review Period' name before you continue!</p>
              </div>
            </a>
          </div>
          <div id="collapse1" class="accordion-body collapse">
            <div class="accordion-inner">
              <dl>
          <dt>What is a Period?</dt>
          <dd>A Period, also known as 'Review Period' is a range of dates that consist of a start and end date of a review period. Typically for an organization this will be the same as the organization calander year.</dd><br>

          <dt>Period examples.</dt>
          <dd>Period Name: <span class="label label-info">Company Review Period 2012</span></dd>
          <dd>Period Start Date: <span class="label label-info">01/02/2012</span></dd>
          <dd>Period End Date: <span class="label label-info">31/01/2013</span></dd><br>

          <dt>How to configure a Period?</dt>
          <dd>If this is your first time configuring a Period, a default Period has been created for you during your account sign-up. To configure your period, click the 'Period' shortcut in the 'Quick Shortcuts' box on the right.</dd>
        </dl>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    <% else %>
      <p>There are no messages...</p>
    <% end %>
  </div> <!-- /widget-content -->
</div> <!-- /widget -->